@11827    = ~Iron Mary's Reply~
@11828    = ~"Iron" Mary of Tantras was a woman of stunning beauty and deadly serious resolve. Iron Mary was easily spotted among her dark-haired mercenary company. Not deigning to wear a helmet, she knew her long blonde hair was visible from across a battlefield. Mary was often hired to track down groups of criminals in lawless lands and put an end to their activities. After five years, troublemakers throughout the Moonsea and Inner Sea knew that if Iron Mary was on their heels, they had angered someone of considerable importance. Instead of putting up a proper fight, many outlaws would attempt to surrender. Iron Mary never accepted surrender, so her reply was always a deadly sound blast shot into the ears of the fool who dared to try talking his or her way out of impending doom.

STATISTICS:

Damage: 4d6 (magic; Fortitude DC 20 for half)
Special:
  Does not require ammo; attacks in the form of a Shout
  Automatically hits but cannot critically hit
  Deals no physical damage; damage bonuses do not increase the damage of this weapon
  Stunning: All creatures hit by the Shout emitted by this weapon are stunned for 1 second (Fortitude DC 20)
Weight: 5 lb.
Feat Requirement:  Simple Weapon, Crossbow
Type:  Two-handed~
